{"title":"Spotted: New Cannondale SuperSix F-Si XC Mountain Bike with dropped seatstays?","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/27/spotted-new-cannondale-supersix-f-si-xc-mountain-bike-with-dropped-seatstays/","date":1635347084000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted.jpeg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"641\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-800x641.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale F-Si Spotted\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-800x641.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-297x238.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-120x96.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-768x615.jpeg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted.jpeg 1276w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-276352\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Every once in a while, instagram delivers more aspirational travel photos and thinly-veiled advertisements. In fact, if you keep an eye out for posts from certain pro riders, you might just catch a glimpse of an unreleased bike. In 2019 Cannondale updated its rocketship cross country hardtail <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/05/18/cannondale-lefty-ocho-sheds-weight-in-single-crown-standard-steerer-on-new-f-si-xc-hardtail/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">F-Si</a> with a few tweaks and an all-new Lefty Ocho fork…</p><div id=\"attachment_193017\"><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-193017\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1500\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy.jpg 1500w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy-768x461.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy-600x360.jpg 600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy-696x418.jpg 696w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy-1068x641.jpg 1068w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_World-Cup-driveside-muddy-700x420.jpg 700w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-193017\">Photo: Cory Benson</p></div><p>Based on that frame, it looks like we could be seeing a “SuperSix-F-Si” for 2022 with the dropped seat stays, integrated chain catcher, and (we’re assuming) some new plush SAVE micro-suspension.</p><p>Alex Howes of UCI World Team EF Education–Nippo fame, posted an Instagram photo riding what looks to be an exciting new Cannondale hardtail frame. The frame in question looks strikingly similar to the <a href=\"https://www.cannondale.com/en-us/bikes/mountain/trail-bikes/trail/trail-se-1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cannondale Trail SE</a> but adds a lower mounted chain guard, Cannondale Ocho fork, and slick paint job (and is presumably carbon fiber rather than the Trail SE’s aluminum frame).</p><div id=\"attachment_276371\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144642/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-Trail-SE-e1635274247215.jpeg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-276371\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144642/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-Trail-SE-e1635274247215.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale F-Si Spotted Trail SE\" width=\"1280\" height=\"713\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144642/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-Trail-SE-e1635274247215.jpeg 1280w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144642/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-Trail-SE-e1635274247215-297x165.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144642/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-Trail-SE-e1635274247215-800x446.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144642/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-Trail-SE-e1635274247215-120x67.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144642/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-Trail-SE-e1635274247215-768x428.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-276371\">Cannondale Trail SE 1 Photo: Cannondale.com</p></div><p>The current trend at Cannondale has been to <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/24/cannondale-super-six-evo-price-spec-sizes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">drop the seat stays</a> and from the killer performance and sharp accelerations of the SuperSix EVO CX, a SuperSix twist could take F-Si to another level of speed.</p><div id=\"attachment_193007\"><p><a href=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-193007\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1400\" height=\"1050\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve.jpg 1400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve-600x450.jpg 600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve-80x60.jpg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve-265x198.jpg 265w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve-696x522.jpg 696w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve-1068x801.jpg 1068w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cannondale-F-Si-Lefty-Ocho-Carbon_carbon-xc-race-hardtail-mountain-bike_single-sided-single-crown-100mm-fork-strut_trail-curve-560x420.jpg 560w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-193007\">Photo: Cory Benson</p></div><p>Yes — the bike is <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/05/21/first-rides-cannondale-f-si-hardtail-lefty-ocho-fork-on-a-world-cup-xc-course/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">wickedly fast</a> but has more of an old-school look and standover height, thanks to its relatively horizontal top tube. The Cannondale F-Si is a favorite of Brazilian powerhouse Henrique Avancini and is one of the lightest on the World Cup circuit, thanks to the Ocho fork and Hi-Mod construction.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale F-Si Spotted\" width=\"1276\" height=\"1022\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted.jpeg 1276w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-297x238.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-800x641.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-120x96.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/26144648/Cannondale-F-Si-Spotted-768x615.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1276px) 100vw, 1276px\"></a></p><p>Could this be the next iteration of Cannondale’s fast-flying F-Si hardtail? Only time will tell, so stay tuned for more. Check out the current Cannondale F-Si and full suspension<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/05/24/review-the-new-cannondale-scalpel-se-is-trail-rocket-with-an-xc-heart/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> Cannondale Scalpel</a> at <a href=\"https://www.cannondale.com/en-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">cannondale.com.</a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f7e9f75a9b04684e58f026e3105b96b9c291cd0416db59f4f1f687c080a9ff68","category":"Cycling"}